smaller number with the remainder.\n","  * Repeat until the remainder is $0$. The last non-zero remainder is the GCD.\n","  \n","  Example: Find GCD of $48$ and $18$\n","\n","  * Get remainder $48 % 18 = 12$\n","  * Get remainder $18 % 12 = 6$\n","  * Get remainder $12 % 6 = 0$\n","  * Stop when remainder is $0$\n","  * GCD$(48, 18) = 6$\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"cCLXlGkS5SkB"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### **Problem Statement:**\n","\n","Write a recursive function to compute the Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) of two numbers $a$ and $b$."],"metadata":{"id":"Mf0ssAfA4IuX"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def gcd(a, b):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Returns the GCD of a and b using recursion.\n","\n","    Args:\n","        a: first number\n","        b: second number\n","\n","    Returns:\n","        gcd(a,b)\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if b == 0:  # Base case\n","        return a\n","    return gcd(b, a % b)  # Recursive call"],"metadata":{"id":"QIicPvmiBreU"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Example usage\n","print(gcd(48, 18))"],"metadata":{"id":"8MV5G65yBuxv","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1739980243265,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":3,"user":{"displayName":"Somak Das","userId":"03478932487509571783"}},"outputId":"abcf172e-a574-4255-e2c5-c3cf19ef9d0e"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["6\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Palindrome**\n","A palindrome is a word, phrase, number, or sequence that reads the same forward and backward, ignoring spaces, punctuation, and capitalization.\n","\n","Examples of Palindromes\n","* Words: \"madam\", \"racecar\", \"level\"\n","* Numbers: 121, 12321, 1001\n","\n","We can check if a string is a palindrome by reversing it and comparing it to the original.\n","\n","For example:\n","\n","`str = 'racecar'`\n","* Check if `s[0] == s[-1]` (Both = `r`)\n","* Check if `s[1] == s[-2]` (Both = `a`)\n","  \n","  ...\n","\n","* We can stop when we have checked the whole string (check till the middle of the string).\n","\n","If any of the above checks fail, `str` is not a palindrome."],"metadata":{"id":"EF0GnlahB25P"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### **Exercise: Checking If a String is a Palindrome**\n","\n","Write a recursive function to check whether a given string is a palindrome (reads the same forward and backward).\n"],"metadata":{"id":"1s7BJbjyF50m"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n","def is_palindrome(s):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Checks if a string is a palindrome using recursion.\n","\n","    Args:\n","        s: string to check\n","\n","    Returns:\n","        (True/False) whether s is pallindrome or not\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if len(s) <= 1:  # Base case: empty string or single character is always a palindrome\n","        return True\n","    if s[0] != s[-1]:  # First and last characters must match\n","        return False\n","    return is_palindrome(s[1:-1])  # Recursive call with middle substring\n","\n","# Example usage\n","print(is_palindrome(\"racecar\"))  # Output: True\n","print(is_palindrome(\"hello\"))    # Output: False\n"],"metadata":{"id":"hfLybHiHGAcL","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1739982604479,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":4,"user":{"displayName":"Somak Das","userId":"03478932487509571783"}},"outputId":"9d6f9c16-a917-4691-84b5-dcda4e6cd40c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["True\n","False\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### **Towers of Hanoi Problem**\n","\n","The Towers of Hanoi is a classic mathematical puzzle involving three rods and a set of disks of different sizes. The objective is to move all the disks from the source rod to the destination rod, using an auxiliary rod, while following these rules:\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"bbI8MWE4KhEj"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["<img src='https://github.com/sdasfpu/IDS1721_Spring2025/blob/main/resources/Towers_of_Hanoi.png?raw=true' height=400>\n"],"metadata":{"id":"uPNSA89oQgE6"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","Only one disk can be moved at a time.\n","A disk can only be placed on top of a larger disk or an empty rod.\n","All disks must be moved from the source to the destination while following the above rules.\n","\n","The problem can be solved recursively, where moving n disks from the source to the destination can be broken down into the following steps:\n","* Move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary.\n","* Move the nth (largest) disk from source to destination.\n","* Move the n-1 disks from auxiliary to destination.\n","* The minimum number of moves required to solve the Towers of Hanoi problem is $2^n-1$ for $n$ disks.\n","\n","This problem is a great example for backtracking with recursion.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"mXdMMzMzQhWc"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["A solution to the problem for `n=5` can be found in this video.\n","\n","https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BalWjeY2O9g"],"metadata":{"id":"jaOgHT8MEHCH"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### **Exercise: Towers of Hanoi**\n","\n","Write a Python program to implement the Towers of Hanoi for `n` disks.\n","\n","The user should enter the number of disks, and the program should display the sequence of moves required to solve the problem.\n","\n","We can label the towers A, B and C from left to right."],"metadata":{"id":"7nxRi_BALXGs"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def hanoi(n, tower1, tower2, tower3):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Shows the moves for solving Towers of Hanoi problem.\n","\n","    Args:\n","        n: Number of disks to start with\n","        tower1: Label for the first tower  (source)\n","        tower2: Label for the second tower (auxiliary)\n","        tower3: Label for the third tower  (destination)\n","\n","    Returns:\n","        count: The number of steps\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if n == 1:\n","        print(f\"Move disk {n} from tower {tower1} to tower {tower3}\")\n","        return\n","    hanoi(n-1, tower1, tower3, tower2)\n","    print(f\"Move disk {n} from tower {tower1} to tower {tower3}\")\n","    hanoi(n-1,tower2,tower1,tower3)"],"metadata":{"id":"IHiHV2j2REcr","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1741639712692,"user_tz":240,"elapsed":7,"user":{"displayName":"Somak Das","userId":"03478932487509571783"}}},"execution_count":1,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["n=3\n","hanoi(n, \"A\", \"B\", \"C\")"],"metadata":{"id":"B8TBVm4qLGl1","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1741639716042,"user_tz":240,"elapsed":31,"user":{"displayName":"Somak Das","userId":"03478932487509571783"}},"outputId":"e7056c55-0c82-402d-c211-4ed8be78cb8e"},"execution_count":3,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Move disk 1 from tower A to tower C\n","Move disk 2 from tower A to tower B\n","Move disk 1 from tower C to tower B\n","Move disk 3 from tower A to tower C\n","Move disk 1 from tower B to tower A\n","Move disk 2 from tower B to tower C\n","Move disk 1 from tower A to tower C\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"JKxAm4xH0ObX"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]}]}